I dont think `BaseMerkleWitness` needs to be exported, since it's purely an internal (static) helper class - we export `MerkleWitness()` which you can extend
you can define a fully functional merkle witness class like that yourself, and even specify the height of the witness/tree it belongs to

```ts
const HEIGHT = 8;
class MyMerkleWitness extends MerkleWitness(HEIGHT) {}
```

then, the `Witness` is just a type 

```
type Witness = {
    isLeft: boolean;
    sibling: Field;
}[];

let witness = fetchWitnessFor(index);
```

which you can populate with the fetched nodes from your API and pass them into your custom `MyMerkleWitness` constructor like `new MyMerkleWitness(witness)`
